Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a system with the integration of Network Coding (NC) and packet level Forward Error Correction (FEC) to address the demands of high bandwidth, low delay and error resiliency in wireless video communication. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper addresses the challenges of two-way real-time video communication in wireless networks, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on wireless video communication, which is a key application area of multimedia research. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a system with the integration of Network Coding (NC) and user cooperation using Randomized Distributed Space-time Coding (R-DSTC) to improve the performance of wireless video communication. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper does not explicitly address cryptography and security, but these are important considerations in wireless video communication and may be relevant to the proposed system.
